A strong, just and sustainable Victoria

Balit, noogee ba kangooeit biik

Learn more

Informed by over 70 years of support to Victorian communities, Helen Macpherson Smith Trust partners with organisations and peer funders to contribute to meaningful improvement in the lives of Victorians.

Through grants and long-term partnerships, the Trust works to improve outcomes for Victorians.

  • $4.7m

    granted in 2024

  • 13

    organisations supported in 2024

  • $146.5m

    granted since 1951

  • Education

    Addressing educational disadvantage through community-based partnerships.

  • Community

    Building connection, capability and capacity in communities.

Balit, noogee ba kangooeit biik | A strong, just and sustainable Victoria

Helen Macpherson Smith Trust acknowledges the traditional owners of the land on which we work, the Wurundjeri people of the Kulin Nation, and pays respect to elders past, present and emerging. As a mark of respect, the Trust’s vision is featured in Woiwurrung language.
